"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583448","Department of Health","false","2016-09-28","<p>Abortion law is a devolved matter with respect to Northern Ireland. It is therefore for the people of Northern Ireland and their elected representatives in Stormont to consider the need for any change.</p>",,"Baroness Chisholm of Owlpen",,"2016-09-28T14:02:34.857Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583448/answer","Biography information for Baroness Chisholm of Owlpen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583448/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583448/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-09-14","Abortion: Northern Ireland","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what discussions they have had with the Northern Ireland Executive regarding the law with respect to abortion in Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Lord Kennedy of Southwark",,"Lord Kennedy of Southwark","HL1912"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583449","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-09-28","<p>The UK is opposed to the death penalty in all circumstances as a matter of principle. We raise our concerns at the highest level and will continue to do so. The former Prime Minister (the Right Hon. Mr David Cameron) reiterated our position to Indonesian President Joko “Jokowi” Widodo in April. The Parliamentary Under Secretary of State for the Foreign and Commonwealth Office, my hon. Friend the Member for Reading West (Mr Sharma) has expressed his concerns about the executions that took place in July.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-09-28T15:23:36.497Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583449/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583449/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583449/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-09-14","Indonesia: Capital Punishment","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they have made to the government of Indonesia concerning the death penalty.","false","Biography information for Lord Kennedy of Southwark",,"Lord Kennedy of Southwark","HL1913"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583450","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-09-28","<p>The UK has a regular and productive law enforcement dialogue with the Philippine authorities relating to serious crime, including drug trafficking, though we have no intelligence to suggest that drugs are being trafficked from the Philippines to the UK or vice versa. All of our engagement in this area is subject to scrutiny under the Overseas Security and Justice Assistance assessment process.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-09-28T15:24:03.11Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583450/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583450/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583450/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-09-14","Philippines: Drugs","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they have made to the government of the Philippines concerning drug trafficking.","false","Biography information for Lord Kennedy of Southwark",,"Lord Kennedy of Southwark","HL1914"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583451","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-09-26","<p>The UK Government has unreservedly condemned the failed attempt to overthrow the democratically elected government of Turkey on 15 July. Both the Prime Minister and the Foreign Secretary spoke to their Turkish counterparts on the day following the coup attempt. The Minister for Europe and the Americas visited Turkey on 20-21 July to reiterate the UK's support for democracy in Turkey, the first Minister to do so following the coup attempt. During his visit he stressed the need for Turkey to respect human rights and the rule of law, and the importance of taking measures under the State of Emergency that are proportionate and justified. The Foreign Secretary met his Turkish counterpart on 7 September in London.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-09-26T15:26:51.543Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583451/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583451/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583451/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-09-14","Turkey: Politics and Government","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they have made to the government of Turkey concerning that government's response to the attempted <i>coup d'état</i> in July.","false","Biography information for Lord Kennedy of Southwark",,"Lord Kennedy of Southwark","HL1915"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583452","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-09-26","<p>​The British Government's view is that the human rights situation in Zimbabwe has worsened in recent weeks. We have been particularly concerned by police violence in response to recent protests and demonstrations. As set out in the EU Statement of 30 August, the freedom to demonstrate and present petitions is enshrined in the Zimbabwean constitution, along with other fundamental human rights and freedoms, including freedom of expression, assembly and association.</p><p>This Government made a 2015 manifesto commitment to stand up for the rule of law and human rights in Zimbabwe. Zimbabwe remains one of the 30 UK Human Rights Priority Countries, where we monitor and report regularly on human rights and support programmes designed to make abuses less likely. We regularly call, both bilaterally and in partnership with others, for an end to human rights abuses and the restoration of internationally accepted standards.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-09-26T15:48:01.993Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583452/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583452/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583452/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-09-14","Zimbabwe: Human Rights","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their latest assessment of the human rights situation in Zimbabwe.","false","Biography information for Lord Kennedy of Southwark",,"Lord Kennedy of Southwark","HL1916"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583453","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-09-28","<p>The UK is deeply concerned about the appalling human rights situation in the Democratic People’s Republic of Korea (DPRK). The UN Commission of Inquiry report, published in 2014, highlighted the severe and systematic human rights violations perpetrated by the regime on its own people. These include summary executions, torture, lack of judicial process, forced labour and prevention of freedom of expression and religion. There is no evidence that the situation is improving. The UK Government will continue to work closely with partners and through international fora to raise its significant concerns about human rights in the DPRK and press for substantial reforms to improve the lives of North Korean citizens. The UK regularly raises our concerns about human rights violations directly with the regime through our Embassy in Pyongyang. The UK will support the annual resolution on DPRK human rights at the forthcoming UN General Assembly to maintain international attention on that country’s dire human rights record. I include with this answer a copy of the Foreign and Commonwealth Office Human Rights Report 2015 which includes a fuller assessment of the human rights situation in the DPRK.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-09-28T15:24:29.533Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583453/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583453/answer","FCO755_Human_Rights_Report_2015_-_WEB (1).pdf","FCO755_Human_Rights_Report_2015_-_WEB (1).pdf","FCO Human Rights and Democracy Report 2015","FCO Human Rights and Democracy Report 2015","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583453/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-09-14","North Korea: Human Rights","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their latest assessment of the human rights situation in North Korea.","false","Biography information for Lord Kennedy of Southwark",,"Lord Kennedy of Southwark","HL1917"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583454","Department for International Development","false","2016-09-27","<p>DFID funds significant food assistance for internally displaced people in Burma through a number of partners. We do not fund the World Food Programme (WFP) for such assistance, but we are informed of their programming decisions. DFID officials visit Rakhine and Kachin regularly to listen to affected communities. We ensure that WFP is made aware of any concerns raised about their assistance. DFID will monitor the impact of recent changes.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-09-27T13:55:53.577Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583454/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583454/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583454/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-09-14","Burma: World Food Programme","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their response to recent reports about cuts by the World Food Programme in aid to internally displaced people in parts of Rakhine State and Kachin State, Burma.","false","Biography information for Baroness Kinnock of Holyhead",,"Baroness Kinnock of Holyhead","HL1918"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583455","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-09-30","<p>The Government is committed to a free and open press and does not interfere with what the press does and does not publish, as long as the press abides by the law. The new system of independent press self-regulation protects press freedom and the industry develops its own standards and codes. The Independent Press Standards Organisation (IPSO) handles complaints about its members under the Editors' Code of Practice. The Independent Monitor for the Press (IMPRESS) is currently consulting on its new Standards Code.</p>",,"Lord Ashton of Hyde",,"2016-09-30T13:26:15.393Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583455/answer","Biography information for Lord Ashton of Hyde","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583455/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583455/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-09-14","Press: Regulation","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assurances they have received from the media, or its representative bodies, that the issue of children being named before they are charged will be addressed through the new system of press regulation.","false","Biography information for The Earl of Listowel",,"The Earl of Listowel","HL1919"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583456","Department for International Development","false","2016-09-27","<p>My Right Hon Friend, the Secretary of State for International Development, announced an investment of £1.1billion in the Global Fund, including a commitment to double private sector contributions for tackling malaria, up to a maximum of £200million, and £90 million tied to successful delivery against a performance agreement.</p><p>The UK’s investment will fund 40 million bednets to tackle malaria; provide enough lifesaving anti-retroviral therapy for 1.3 million people with HIV; and support the treatment of 800,000 people with tuberculosis.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-09-27T13:56:28.263Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583456/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583456/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/583456/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-09-14","Global Fund to Fight AIDS, Tuberculosis and Malaria","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what steps they are taking to ensure that the replenishment target of the Global Fund to Fight AIDS, Tuberculosis and Malaria is met at the Pledging Conference in Montreal on 16 September.","false","Biography information for Baroness Masham of Ilton",,"Baroness Masham of Ilton","HL1920"
