"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582584","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-10-10","<p>The law requires the welfare of the child to be the court’s paramount concern when making any decision about a child’s upbringing, including with whom the child is to live or spend time. The courts must consider the individual facts of each case when making a decision.</p><p> </p><p>Decisions in these cases are a matter for the independent judiciary.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2016-10-10T14:24:27.927Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582584/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582584/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582584/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-09-13","Children: Custody","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what recent assessment she has made of the equality between mothers and fathers of court judgments on child custody and access to children; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Laurence Robertson","Tewkesbury","Mr Laurence Robertson","46151"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582585","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-09-20","<p>The Government will consider the advantages and disadvantages of remaining in a Customs Union carefully. There are a number of options, and we have made clear that we will pursue one that works for the unique circumstances of the UK.</p><p>The open border for people and businesses has served us well and no-one wants to see a return to the borders of the past. It is a high priority for the Government that we do not see border controls coming into place. There is a very strong commitment from the Irish government as well as ourselves to see that that does not happen. We must now work closely together to ensure that as the UK leaves the EU we find shared solutions to the challenges and maximise the opportunities for both the UK and the Republic of Ireland.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-09-20T14:29:38.627Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582585/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582585/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582585/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-09-13","Borders: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what assessment he has made of the potential effect of UK withdrawal from the EU Customs Union on the policy that there should be no border checks between Northern Ireland and Ireland.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart C. McDonald","46165"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582586","Prime Minister","false","2016-10-10","<p>The Department for Education is in charge of the apprenticeships policy. I will continue to make any appointments, as they are required, to deliver the government’s agenda.</p><p> </p>","Maidenhead","Mrs Theresa May",,"2016-10-10T08:20:13.957Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582586/answer","Biography information for Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582586/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582586/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2016-09-13","Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, if she will appoint a new Apprenticeships Adviser.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","46313"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582587","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-10","<p>The Highway Code makes it clear that drivers need to be in control of their vehicles at all times. That means that drivers need to ensure that they use any device in their vehicles in a safe way when driving.</p><p> </p><p>Driving while using a hands-free kit is legal and previously published research estimated that whilst a hands-free kit is distracting, it is safer than using a hand-held device.</p><p> </p><p>Many cars now have built in hands-free kits and we are working with the industry to ensure that safety and legislation keeps pace with new technology as it develops.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","46310 ; 46312","2016-10-10T10:02:05.23Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582587/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582587/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582587/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-09-13","Driving: Mobile Phones","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what evidence his Department has received which shows that using a hands-free kit while driving is any less dangerous than using a hand-held phone.","false","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire","46311"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582588","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-10","<p>The Highway Code makes it clear that drivers need to be in control of their vehicles at all times. That means that drivers need to ensure that they use any device in their vehicles in a safe way when driving.</p><p> </p><p>Driving while using a hands-free kit is legal and previously published research estimated that whilst a hands-free kit is distracting, it is safer than using a hand-held device.</p><p> </p><p>Many cars now have built in hands-free kits and we are working with the industry to ensure that safety and legislation keeps pace with new technology as it develops.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","46310 ; 46311","2016-10-10T10:02:05.307Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582588/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582588/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582588/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-09-13","Driving: Mobile Phones","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will take steps to prohibit the use of hands-free kits by drivers of commercial coaches.","false","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire","46312"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582589","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-10","<p>As set out in the previous answer, we are committed to improving compensation arrangements for passengers and we expect to make an announcement on this shortly.</p><p> </p><p>We want to strengthen the rights of rail passengers to get compensation for poor service. The Consumer Rights Act will allow rail passengers to challenge compensation amounts awarded for delays and cancellations where the train operator is at fault.</p><p> </p><p>Train operators’ existing compensation schemes will continue to provide the main means of redress for passengers after 1 October 2016, when the Act comes into force for all transport providers. We will continue to work with train operators to improve their compensation schemes.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2016-10-10T10:46:49.787Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582589/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582589/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582589/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-09-13","Railways: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 20 June 2016 to Question 40383, when he plans to make an announcement on when passengers will have access to compensation when trains are over 15 minutes late; whether the application of the Consumer Rights Act 2015 (CRA) from 1 October 2016 will affect that access; after how many minutes of delay the consumer's right to claim a full refund under the CRA will take effect; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","46147"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582590","Department for Transport","false","2016-09-20","<p>Mobility scooters have to comply with the prescribed conditions and requirements set out in the ‘Use of Invalid Carriages on Highways Regulations 1988’ which divides them into two main categories.</p><p> </p><p>The Class 2 type can travel at 4mph and is primarily intended for use on the footway or footpath. 4 mph is considered appropriate for pavement use as it is akin to a brisk walking pace.</p><p> </p><p>The Class 3 type can travel on the road at up to 8 mph, but must have the facility via a limiter to be driven at no more than 4 mph when used on the footpath.</p><p> </p><p>Users of new or second hand Class 3 vehicles are required to register their vehicles with the Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency (DVLA) for use on public roads. However, there is currently no requirement to display the vehicle registration number on the scooter and I have no plans to change this.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-09-20T14:26:23.147Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582590/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582590/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582590/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-09-13","Invalid Vehicles: Vehicle Number Plates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will make plans to introduce number plates for all mobility scooters to ensure that such scooters could be traced in the event of a collision with a pedestrian.","false","Biography information for Kevin Foster","Torbay","Kevin Foster","46139"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582591","Department for Transport","false","2016-09-16","<p>DfT officials have had some early conversations with local authorities about the possibilities for coordinating/improving transport delivery across the Solent area as part of potential combined authority proposals. Discussions across Government are still ongoing.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2016-09-16T14:10:29.34Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582591/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582591/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582591/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-09-13","Roads: South East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what discussions his Department has had with (a) local authorities and (b) other organisations on which (i) key net roads and (ii) highway responsibilities could be devolved to the proposed Solent combined authority.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Turner","Isle of Wight","Mr Andrew Turner","46154"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582592","Department for Transport","false","2016-09-21","<p>The Department does not hold any information on the destination of employees, or their previous work history so is unable to provide an estimation or confirm numbers of staff<em>.</em></p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2016-09-21T07:44:45.653Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582592/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582592/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582592/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-09-13","Department for Transport: Heathrow Airport Limited","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate he has made of the number of staff (a) departing from his Department who accepted jobs with Heathrow Airport Limited and (b) arriving in his Department from Heathrow Airport Limited in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","46248"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582593","Department for Transport","false","2016-09-21","<p>We launched the second round of our New Stations Fund on 26 August, with up to £20 million available to promoters of new stations throughout England and Wales. Successful bids may be awarded up to 75% towards the capital expenditure on the station.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2016-09-21T11:21:16.403Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582593/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582593/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582593/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-09-13","Railway Stations: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps his Department is taking to encourage the construction of new railway stations along the England-Wales border.","false","Biography information for Chris Elmore","Ogmore","Chris Elmore","46251"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582594","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-10","<p>The government is currently considering the case for electrification of the line between Selby and Hull in light of the intention by Hull First Trains to invest in a new bi-mode fleet. The government will announce its decision in due course.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2016-10-10T15:56:35.647Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582594/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582594/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582594/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-09-13","Selby-Hull Railway Line: Electrification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what progress his Department has made on the electrification of the Hull to Selby rail line; and what his provisional timeline is for those works to be completed.","false","Biography information for Karl Turner","Kingston upon Hull East","Karl Turner","46264"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582595","Department for Transport","false","2016-09-21","<p>A copy of the memorandum of understanding will be placed in the House library.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2016-09-21T11:12:18.877Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582595/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582595/answer","160915 MOU between DfT, CAA, HO, Police.pdf","160915 MOU between DfT, CAA, HO, Police.pdf","Memorandum of understanding","Memorandum of understanding","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582595/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-09-13","Unmanned Air Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 15 June 2016 to Question 40016, on unmanned air vehicles, if he will place in the Library a copy of the memorandum of understanding between his Department, the Home Office, the Civil Aviation Authority and the police.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","46266"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582596","Department for Transport","false","2016-09-21","<p>The Secretary of State for Transport has not received any requests for such permissions in the last two years.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2016-09-21T08:33:21.347Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582596/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582596/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582596/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-09-13","Unmanned Air Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what permissions have been sought by (a) NATO, (b) the US and (c) any other country to fly remotely piloted aircraft systems in UK airspace in the last two years.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","46267"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582597","Department for Transport","false","2016-09-21","<p>Amazon is currently testing a developmental‎ drone delivery system in the UK, within a defined and contained test site area on private land. Trials involving customers are not part of this testing. Prior to the current trials starting, an operational safety case was assessed and approved by the Civil Aviation Authority, which ‎took into consideration the risk and mitigation of damage to other aircraft and infrastructure in the test area. The trial is designed in compliance with all regulatory and legal requirements.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2016-09-21T08:06:32.56Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582597/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582597/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582597/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-09-13","Amazon: Unmanned Air Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether Amazon's testing of parcel delivery by drone has begun; and what arrangements have been agreed for safety, insurance and data protection during this trial.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","46270"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582598","Department for Transport","false","2016-09-20","<p>The Government will review Highways England’s existing performance indicators and targets when setting the next Road Investment Strategy. As part of this process the Government will consider whether existing indicators and targets should be strengthened, and whether new indicators should be introduced.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2016-09-20T08:59:50.887Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582598/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582598/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582598/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-09-13","Highways England: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will introduce stronger key performance indicators to evaluate the performance of Highways England.","false","Biography information for Mark Pritchard","The Wrekin","Mark Pritchard","46280"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582599","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-10","<p>The Highway Code makes it clear that drivers need to be in control of their vehicles at all times. That means that drivers need to ensure that they use any device in their vehicles in a safe way when driving.</p><p> </p><p>Driving while using a hands-free kit is legal and previously published research estimated that whilst a hands-free kit is distracting, it is safer than using a hand-held device.</p><p> </p><p>Many cars now have built in hands-free kits and we are working with the industry to ensure that safety and legislation keeps pace with new technology as it develops.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","46311 ; 46312","2016-10-10T10:02:05.167Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582599/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582599/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582599/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-09-13","Driving: Mobile Phones","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment his Department has made of the dangers of using a hands-free kit while driving.","false","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire","46310"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582600","Department for Transport","false","2016-09-21","<p>The European Aviation Safety Agency (EASA) has requirements in the aircraft certification specifications regarding the ventilation requirements of aircraft cabin, but no maximum temperature has been identified. It would be for EASA to introduce any changes to these safety requirements, based on robust evidence base.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2016-09-21T07:56:15.53Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582600/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582600/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582600/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-09-13","Aircraft: Temperature","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will introduce a statutory maximum temperature on (a) stationary aircraft and (b) aircraft in flight.","false","Biography information for Mark Pritchard","The Wrekin","Mark Pritchard","46279"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582601","Department for Transport","false","2016-09-21","<p>The Government encourages and welcomes innovative proposals and solutions from industry which seek to safely unlock services and benefits delivered by drones. This could include improving mobile data coverage for difficult to reach and remote areas in the UK and other countries. However, there are no current discussions or proposals with industry to provide such a service.</p><p> </p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2016-09-21T08:39:44.653Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582601/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582601/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582601/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-09-13","Unmanned Air Vehicles: Mobile Phones","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what trials his Department have (a) proposed and (b) undertaken on the use of drones to provide mobile data coverage in remote areas.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","46268"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582602","Department for Transport","false","2016-09-21","<p>The department will aim to publish its report of the public dialogue on remotely piloted aircraft systems and small drones in the UK later this year.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2016-09-21T08:30:53.03Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582602/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582602/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582602/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-09-13","Unmanned Air Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will publish the report of the public dialogue on remotely piloted aircraft systems and small drones in UK airspace.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","46269"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582603","Cabinet Office","false","2016-10-10","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2016-10-10T08:35:27.66Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582603/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582603/answer","PQ46308 v.02.pdf","PQ46308 v.02.pdf","UKSA Letter to Member - Hospitality Industry ","UKSA Letter to Member - Hospitality Industry ","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582603/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-09-13","Service Industries: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what proportion of the hospitality industry workforce in (a) Cumbria and (b) Westmorland and Lonsdale constituency was born in another EU country.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","46308"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582604","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-10-10","<p>DWP are undertaking work to investigate the issue of rent arrears in Universal Credit, it aims to understand the true level of rent arrears and what is causing them. We expect to know a lot more about this issue as the work progresses and following the analysis of the next Universal Credit Gateway Survey which we will be publishing later this year.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2016-10-10T15:47:40.457Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582604/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582604/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582604/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-13","Rents: Arrears","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what plans his Department has to monitor the effect on housing rent arrears of the length of time taken for initial payment of universal credit.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","46257"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582605","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-10-10","<p>Universal Credit Claimants who are gainfully self-employed and within one year of starting out in self-employment are also eligible for a ‘start-up period’, of up to one year to support them to grow their business.</p><p>Claimants who are in their start-up period will attend quarterly sessions designed to provide support, assistance and guidance. They will have access to a cadre of work coaches with the right skills to signpost self-employed people to support to grow their business and earnings.</p><p>We will use survey findings to ensure that the journey for newly self-employed claimants of Universal Credit is effective.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2016-10-10T15:25:26.237Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582605/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582605/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582605/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-13","Universal Credit: Self-employed","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps he is taking to ensure that universal credit is effective in supporting an increasing number of people into self-employment.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","46259"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582606","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-10-10","<p>Universal Credit has introduced Personal Budgeting Support to provide budgeting and money advice to claimants as part of Universal Support provisions. We have engaged with all 380 local authorities in delivering this.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2016-10-10T15:51:52.207Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582606/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582606/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582606/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-13","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, with how many local authorities his Department has worked to improve budgeting advice for universal credit claimants.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","46260"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582607","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-10-10","<p>The Health and Safety Executive (HSE) does not hold this information. However, HSE recognises that poorly designed shift-working arrangements and long working hours can result in fatigue, accidents, injuries and ill health and has produced guidance for employers on designing and implementing shift-working arrangements:</p><p>(<a href="http://www.hse.gov.uk/humanfactors/topics/fatigue.htm" target="_blank">http://www.hse.gov.uk/humanfactors/topics/fatigue.htm</a>).</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-10-10T16:16:17.767Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582607/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582607/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582607/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-13","Mining: Industrial Health and Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 7 September 2016 to Question 44365, what assessment the Health and Safety Executive has made on the effect of long shift patterns on the incidence of (a) errors, (b) accidents and (c) injuries in (i) all sectors of the workforce and (ii) the mining industry.","false","Biography information for Tom Blenkinsop","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Tom Blenkinsop","46238"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582608","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-09-20","<p>The study has been commissioned. The timing and content are being considered. The honourable member for Redcar and other members of the SSI taskforce will be informed when more information is available.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2016-09-20T14:18:30.693Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582608/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582608/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582608/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-13","Sahaviriya Steel Industries UK: Redcar","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, by what date his Department plans to complete its longitudinal study into former employees of SSI UK; what the likely outcome of that study will be; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Anna Turley","Redcar","Anna Turley","46135"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582609","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-10-10","<p>The Secretary of State confirms that a claimant requires an appointee if we receive unequivocal medical evidence as to the claimant’s capacity to manage their benefit claim or if, as in the vast majority of cases, the visiting officer, through a series of questions relating to the comprehension of claiming and managing a benefit award, will reach a conclusion as to their capacity to act for themselves. This is specifically a benefit-related capacity assessment and not a mental capacity assessment.</p><p>Once someone has been appointed, they will remain in that role until (a) they wish to relinquish it (b) they themselves lose capacity (c) the claimant regains capacity or (d) they abuse their position by not acting in the best interests of the claimant and the appointment is revoked. This latter requirement is stressed to the prospective appointee when the appointment is being considered and they are required to sign form BF56 to confirm that they understand their responsibilities. The Department also has a review system in place.</p><p>The vast majority of revocations of an appointeeship occur because of information received from a third party alleging financial abuse which is subsequently confirmed on investigation.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","46143 ; 46144","2016-10-10T13:57:32.537Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582609/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582609/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582609/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-13","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how his Department assesses whether benefit appointees should be appointed; what factors are taken into account in such cases by the assessor; and what the requirements relating to the mental capacity of adult benefit recipients are in such cases.","false","Biography information for Andrew Selous","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous","46142"
