dfordshire","Andrew Selous","46144"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582612","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-09-21","<p>The UK is a world leader in supporting vulnerable people fleeing conflicts around the world and, as such, we have established an effective system to accommodate and shelter resettled people.</p><p>Refugees and those who have humanitarian protection status, such as persons resettled under the Syrian Vulnerable Persons Resettlement Programme, are entitled to work and have access to some benefits upon arrival.</p><p>DWP has decided that the application of the Past Presence Test (PPT) should not apply to refugees for Disability Living Allowance (DLA) and are currently considering how best to implement that change, including the impact to other benefits which use a similar PPT.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-09-21T15:24:02.717Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582612/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582612/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582612/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-13","Refugees: Syria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the implications for his policies of the finding in the report by the National Audit Office, The Syrian Vulnerable Persons Resettlement Programme, published in September 2016, that lack of access by resettled Syrians to personal independence payments and carer's allowance may cause difficulties to some refugees and have a negative impact on their experiences.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart C. McDonald","46164"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582613","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-10-10","<p>We will publish a Green Paper later this year.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-10-10T11:26:20.233Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582613/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582613/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582613/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-13","Employment: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when the Government plans to publish its green paper on disability employment.","false","Biography information for Liz McInnes","Heywood and Middleton","Liz McInnes","46323"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582614","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-10-10","<p>The Department does not routinely collect information on the numbers of people who have had to return a Motability vehicle nor on whether they were successful on appeal. Motability is an independent charitable organisation that is wholly responsible for the administration of the Motability scheme, including collating its own management information. Whilst the Department meets regularly with Motability to discuss scheme performance, questions relating to the details of the scheme’s operation should be directed to Motability itself.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-10-10T15:15:28.427Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582614/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582614/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582614/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-13","Motability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many claimants have lost their entitlement to motability cars during their reassessment from disability living allowance to personal independence payment; and how many such claimants have subsequently had their motability cars reinstated following an appeal to the first-tier tribunal in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","46329"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582615","Department of Health","false","2016-10-10","<p>This matter is under consideration as part of work on the forthcoming Green Paper on work and health.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2016-10-10T10:24:55.293Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582615/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582615/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582615/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-09-13","Employment: Medical Records","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent steps he has taken to ensure that work status is routinely recorded in health records.","false","Biography information for Liz McInnes","Heywood and Middleton","Liz McInnes","46324"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582616","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-10-10","<p>The Government is considering the recommendations of the Law Commission and will respond in due course.</p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2016-10-10T13:20:34.003Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582616/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582616/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582616/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-09-13","Retail Trade: Insolvency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, when he will respond to the Report of the Law Commission Consumer Prepayments on Retailer Insolvency HC543, published on 13 July 2016.","false","Biography information for Jessica Morden","Newport East","Jessica Morden","46332"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582617","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-10-25","<p>A successful industrial strategy can only be developed by engaging with people, businesses and organisations across the country. As the Government’s Industrial Strategy develops, the Ministerial team in the Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy will continue to travel to all parts of the UK and engage with a wide range of stakeholders, including Industrial Partnerships.</p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2016-10-25T08:21:01.843Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582617/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582617/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582617/answer","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582617/answer/previousversion/13132","Biography information for Jesse Norman","201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-09-13","Industry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what role Industrial Partnerships will play in delivering the Government's Industrial Strategy.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","46314"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582618","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-09-21","<p>The Government has no plans to introduce a statutory workplace maximum temperature. For information on the existing law and guidance on workplace temperature, I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 09 September 2016 to Question UIN <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=44106" target="_blank">44106</a>.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-09-21T14:54:32.093Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582618/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582618/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582618/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-13","Working Conditions: Temperature","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will make it his policy to introduce a statutory  workplace maximum temperature.","false","Biography information for Mark Pritchard","The Wrekin","Mark Pritchard","46283"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582619","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-10-10","<p>The Department’s activity to tackle climate change cuts across the work of various teams and is undertaken by officials across a number of professions, including policy advisors, scientists, engineers and economists. In addition the Department has access to a range of experts from outside the Department including academia and organisations such as the Met Office Hadley Centre. Consequently, it is not possible to provide an exact number of officials who could be called climate change experts.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2016-10-10T11:11:49.733Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582619/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582619/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582619/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-09-13","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, pursuant to the Answer of 12 September 2016 to Question 45149, how many climate change experts are employed by his Department; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","46321"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582620","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-10-18","<p>The Government has made changes to the Renewable Heat Incentive (RHI) Scheme Regulations 2011, and these amendments came into force on 1 August 2016.</p><p>The changes therefore apply to all new biomass-Combined Heat and Power plant with an accreditation date on or after 1 August 2016.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2016-10-18T11:03:00.52Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582620/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582620/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582620/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-09-13","Biofuels: Renewable Heat Incentive Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether he will allow combined heat and power biomass plants pre-accredited under the Renewable Heat Incentive that are in-build but not yet in receipt of full accreditation to remain eligible under the rules of the scheme which prevailed at the time of the initial investment.","false","Biography information for Nigel Adams","Selby and Ainsty","Nigel Adams","46162"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582621","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-10-10","<p>In the period from November 2014 to August 2016, inclusive, the Insolvency Service has placed 3,907 newspaper advertisements and 44,452 notices were placed in the London Gazette. All of these were in the performance of statutory functions by official receivers in relation to the administration of bankruptcies of individuals and the compulsory liquidation of companies. The Insolvency Service has not placed any advertisements through any of the other types of outlet listed in the question.</p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2016-10-10T13:17:11.03Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582621/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582621/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582621/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-09-13","Insolvency Service: Advertising","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many advertisements the Insolvency Service has placed (a) in newspapers, (b) in magazines, (c) on television, (d) on social media, (e) on transport and (f) on radio since November 2014.","false","Biography information for Jessica Morden","Newport East","Jessica Morden","46148"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582622","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-10-10","<p>My Rt Hon Friend the Secretary of State for Business Energy and Industrial Strategy, has not held discussions with HM Treasury on the use of Farepak unclaimed funds in 2019; Farepak creditors will still be able to make claims for monies they are owed when they are handed over where the claims were accepted as valid by the joint liquidators.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2016-10-10T16:54:40.657Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582622/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582622/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582622/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-09-13","Farepak","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what discussions he has had with HM Treasury on the use of Farepak unclaimed funds in 2019.","false","Biography information for Jessica Morden","Newport East","Jessica Morden","46149"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582623","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-10-10","<p>The current value of Farepak unclaimed funds is £1,007,267.41.</p><p> </p><p>The agency will hold the funds for the next six years, people can however continue to claim indefinitely. The Insolvency Service has liaised with media outlets and the matter has been covered by BBC Moneybox, MoneySaving Expert and BBC Watchdog, to draw attention to any unpaid creditor or has yet to come forward.</p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2016-10-10T13:11:42.02Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582623/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582623/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582623/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-09-13","Farepak","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what the current value is of Farepak unclaimed funds.","false","Biography information for Jessica Morden","Newport East","Jessica Morden","46150"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582624","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-10-18","<p>The Government has made changes to the Renewable Heat Incentive (RHI) Scheme Regulations 2011, and these amendments came into force on 1 August 2016.</p><p>The changes were made to ensure appropriate value for money for the taxpayer. The decision to make the changes was informed by market intelligence, scheme data and consultation responses.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2016-10-18T12:49:19.773Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582624/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582624/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582624/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-09-13","Biofuels: Renewable Heat Incentive Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment his Department has made of the relative merits of changing the (a) subsidy structure and (b) tariff rate with reference to the administration of the non-domestic Renewable Heat Incentive for biomass combined heat and power generators.","false","Biography information for Nigel Adams","Selby and Ainsty","Nigel Adams","46160"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582625","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-10-03","<p>The Government has made changes to the Renewable Heat Incentive (RHI) Scheme Regulations 2011. These amendments came into force on 1 August 2016. The regulations require Ofgem to apply the new rules to all new biomass-Combined Heat and Power plant with an accreditation date on or after 1 August 2016.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2016-10-03T12:38:21.973Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582625/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582625/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582625/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-09-13","Biofuels: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what guidance his Department has given to Ofgem on whether the new subsidy structure relating to low electrical output combined heat and power solid biomass generators should apply to those generators that are (a) funded, (b) built and (c) in-build and already in receipt of pre-accreditation certificates.","false","Biography information for Nigel Adams","Selby and Ainsty","Nigel Adams","46161"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582626","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-09-23","<p>In March the Department for Energy and Climate Change published a consultation “The Renewable Heat Incentive: A reformed and refocused scheme”, including proposals relating to solar thermal.</p><p>The Government is currently considering responses to the consultation and will announce its final proposals in due course.</p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2016-09-23T13:35:20.82Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582626/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582626/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582626/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-09-13","Solar Power: Renewable Heat Incentive Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether he plans to retain solar thermal under the Renewable Heat Incentive for (a) domestic and smaller commercial heating applications and (b) new applications including space heating and community heating.","false","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","46250"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582627","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-09-23","<p>The details of the forthcoming Contract for Difference (CfD) allocation round, including whether funding for wave and tidal stream projects should be ring-fenced, will be announced in due course.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2016-09-23T13:36:26.18Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582627/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582627/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582627/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-09-13","Water Power: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether his Department plans to continue to ring-fence Contracts for Difference funding solely for tidal and marine energy projects.","false","Biography information for Richard Graham","Gloucester","Richard Graham","46245"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582628","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-09-23","<p>In March the Department for Energy and Climate Change published a consultation “The Renewable Heat Incentive: A reformed and refocused scheme”, including proposals relating to solar thermal.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is currently considering responses to the consultation and will announce its final proposals in due course.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2016-09-23T13:35:05.037Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582628/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582628/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582628/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-09-13","Solar Power: Renewable Heat Incentive Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, if he will take steps to review the decision to remove solar thermal from the Renewable Heat Incentive.","false","Biography information for Matthew Pennycook","Greenwich and Woolwich","Matthew Pennycook","46246"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582629","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-10-10","<p>Energy performance certificates on sale, rent or build, are a requirement of the Energy Performance of Buildings Regulations, which implemented the Recast of the Energy Performance of Buildings Directive in England and Wales. Until exit negotiations are concluded, the UK remains a full member of the European Union and all the rights and obligations of EU membership remain in force. Therefore the requirement for energy performance certificates will continue to apply.</p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2016-10-10T15:25:05.84Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582629/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582629/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582629/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-09-13","Housing: Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether it is his policy to continue the use of energy efficiency assessments when renting out or selling domestic properties; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Laurence Robertson","Tewkesbury","Mr Laurence Robertson","46183"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582630","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-10-10","<p>I have not received any such representations.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2016-10-10T16:55:53.04Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582630/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582630/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582630/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-09-13","ARM","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what representations he has received from (a) employees of and (b) agencies connected with ARM Holdings plc on the takeover of that business; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Laurence Robertson","Tewkesbury","Mr Laurence Robertson","46184"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582631","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-10-10","<p>Solar in the UK has been a success story with 11 gigawatts deployed, over 99% of which has been delivered under Conservative-led Governments since May 2010.</p><p>Changes to the Feed-in Tariff scheme were introduced in 2016 to manage costs and ensure value for money. We note the efforts that the solar industry is making to adapt to the revised scheme. We have received the report ‘Seeing through the gloom’ and noted its findings.</p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2016-10-10T11:12:08.67Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582631/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582631/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582631/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-09-13","Solar Power: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether he has made an assessment of the implications for his Department's policies of the report, Seeing through the gloom, UK solar seeks stability after subsidy cut, published in July 2016.","false","Biography information for Mr Ben Bradshaw","Exeter","Mr Ben Bradshaw","46185"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582632","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-09-23","<p>Almost 11 GW of solar capacity has now been installed. Solar continues to deploy under the Feed-in Tariff scheme, with over 140 MW of applications since the scheme reopened in February.</p><p>Changes to the Feed-in Tariff scheme were introduced in 2016 to manage costs and ensure value for money. While it is appropriate to allow for a period of stability following these changes, the Secretary of State continues to keep the performance of the scheme under review.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2016-09-23T13:34:50.437Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582632/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582632/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582632/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-09-13","Solar Power: Feed-in Tariffs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what his policy is on reform of the feed-in tariff for solar generation.","false","Biography information for Matthew Pennycook","Greenwich and Woolwich","Matthew Pennycook","46265"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582633","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-09-28","<p>The Government has various policies in place that will support pensioners and other vulnerable people with their energy bills throughout winter 2016/17,irrespective of temperature.</p><p> </p><p>The Warm Home Discount scheme provides eligible households with a £140 energy bill rebate. This winter, over 2 million low income and vulnerable households, of which over 1.2 million are pensioner households, will be helped under the scheme.</p><p> </p><p>Over 12 million pensioners receive the Winter Fuel Payment of up to £300 each winter while people on certain benefits, including Pension Credit, receive a £25 Cold Weather Payment for each seven day period of freezing temperatures.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is also reforming the Energy Company Obligation to have a greater focus on vulnerable and low income households. It will have a value of £640m a year, will run from 2017 until 2022, and and homes helped under the new obligation could see their energy bills fall by up to £300 per year.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, we are providing £1.3m to fund the Big Energy Saving Network and running the Big Energy Saving Week again. This is a grant scheme that supports vulnerable consumers to take action to reduce their energy costs by switching supplier and taking up energy efficiency, through outreach by trusted and trained community and third sector organisations.</p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2016-09-28T13:03:41.267Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582633/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582633/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582633/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-09-13","Older People: Weather","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what contingency plans the Government has in place for winter 2016-17 to support pensioners and other vulnerable people in the event of a prolonged spell of below average temperatures.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","46271"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582634","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-09-27","<p><strong> </strong></p><p>Fuel poverty is measured at the household level. We do not publish the number of children in fuel poverty as we cannot accurately estimate personal level information.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2016-09-27T10:23:57.457Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582634/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582634/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582634/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-09-13","Fuel Poverty: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many children in England were classed as living in fuel poverty in each year since May 2011.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","46272"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582635","Department for International Trade","false","2016-10-10","<p>Since the inception of the department, as part of their official duties Ministers and accompanying officials have visited:</p><p>Rt. Hon Friend the Secretary of State for International Trade (Liam Fox) - USA, India, Switzerland, Bahrain, United Arab Emirates, Qatar, Northern Ireland, Scotland.</p><p>Rt. Hon Friend the Minister of State (Greg Hands) - USA, Germany, Taiwan, Korea.</p><p>Hon Friend the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State (Mark Garnier) - Burma, Thailand, Israel, France.</p><p>Noble Friend the Minister of State (Lord Price CVO) - China, South Korea, USA, Germany, Brazil, Switzerland, Czech Republic, Hungary, Slovakia.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-10-10T11:56:01.357Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582635/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582635/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582635/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-09-13","Department for International Trade: Travel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, pursuant to the Answer of 12 September to Question 45236, to which destinations (a) ministers and (b) officials have taken flights as part of their official duties since his Department was established.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","46309"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582636","Department for International Trade","false","2016-09-20","<p>Following her appointment on 13 July 2016 the Prime Minister established the Department for International Trade (DIT).</p><p>Until such time as a transfer of functions order establishes the Secretary of State as a corporation sole, the Department for International Trade remains a unified Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) and Department for Business, Energy &amp; Industrial Strategy (BEIS) department for accounting purposes.</p><p>As the Department for International Trade is being formed, accurate data for overseas flights is unavailable.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-09-20T13:58:55.03Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582636/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582636/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582636/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-09-13","Department for International Trade: Travel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many international flights have been taken by (a) Ministers, (b) civil servants and (c) special advisers in his Department in an official capacity since his Department was created.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","46207"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582637","Department for International Trade","false","2016-09-20","<p>Following her appointment on 13 July 2016 the Prime Minister established the Department for International Trade (DIT). The DIT aggregates UK Trade and Investment (UKTI), UK Export and Finance (UKEF), Trade Policy Units from the Department for Business, Energy &amp; Industrial Strategy (BEIS).</p><p> </p><p>Until such time as a transfer of functions order establishes the Secretary of State as a corporation sole, DIT remains a unified Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) and Department for Business, Energy &amp; Industrial Strategy (BEIS) department for accounting purposes.</p><p> </p><p>As DIT is currently being formed, accurate data for overnight accommodation spend is unavailable.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-09-20T13:57:03.887Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582637/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582637/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582637/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-09-13","Department for International Trade: Hotels","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how much his Department has spent on overnight accommodation since it was created.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","46208"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582638","Department for International Trade","false","2016-10-10","<p>As we leave the EU, Britain will seek to become the global leader in free trade. Ministers and officials in the Department for International Trade are making overseas visits to a wide range of markets, in order to promote the UK as a great place to do business and with which to trade. Through these discussions, we are working to ensure we take advantage of all the opportunities available to us, including through our future trading relationships.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-10-10T16:29:08.937Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582638/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582638/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582638/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-09-13","Department for International Trade: Visits Abroad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many overseas visits he has made for the purpose of negotiating trade deals since his appointment as Secretary of State.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","46319"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582639","Department for International Trade","false","2016-10-10","<p>The EU has trade agreements in place with 23 Commonwealth countries.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-10-10T16:42:53.067Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582639/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582639/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582639/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-09-13","Trade Agreements: Commonwealth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many trade deals the UK has with other Commonwealth countries.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","46317"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582640","Department for International Trade","false","2016-10-10","<p>The newly created Department for International Trade (DIT) has been forged out of the forerunner (non-ministerial) Departments UK Trade and Investment (UKTI), UK Export Finance (UKEF) and has assumed Trade Policy Unit responsibilities previously held by the Department for Business Innovation and Skills (BIS).</p><p> </p><p>Until such time as a transfer of functions order establishes the Secretary of State as a corporation sole, DIT remains a unified Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) and Department for Business, Energy &amp; Industrial Strategy (BEIS) department for accounting purposes.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-10-10T11:58:12.483Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582640/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582640/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582640/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-09-13","Department for International Trade: Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, if he will estimate the total amount his Department has spent to date.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","46333"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582641","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-10-10","<p>The Prime Minister has been clear that we will trigger Article 50 b​efore the end of​ March 2017. The process for leaving the EU and determining our future relationship will clearly not be brief or straightforward, so we need to take time to think through our objectives and approach. We want to get the best deal for Britain, not the quickest one. We recognise the need to create certainty as soon as possible but also to get negotiations off to the right start.</p><p> </p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones",,"2016-10-10T16:21:22Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582641/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582641/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582641/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-09-13","Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, pursuant to the Answer of 12 September 2016 to Question 43456; when he expects the objectives and approach of the UK to negotiations with the EU to be agreed.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","46334"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582642","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-10-10","<p>Britain has been at the forefront of the free trade-supporting countries in the EU for the last 40 years. The Department for Exiting the EU now has over 200 staff plus the expertise of over 120 officials in Brussels, and is growing fast. The overall size and scope of the new department, including staffing and budget, are regularly reviewed. We will ensure we are appropriately staffed to deal with all aspects of the forthcoming negotiation.</p><p> </p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones",,"2016-10-10T16:17:59.027Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582642/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582642/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582642/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-09-13","Department for Exiting the European Union: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many negotiators his Department has recruited.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","46318"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582643","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-10-10","<p>The Department for Exiting the European Union (DExEU) is properly resourced. Detailed work is underway to establish the final budget required and this will be voted on and published as part of the Supplementary Estimate process. Total expenditure by the Department will be set out in the Annual Report and Accounts in the usual way.</p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones",,"2016-10-10T16:15:38.64Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582643/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582643/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582643/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-09-13","Department for Exiting the European Union: Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, pursuant to the Answer of 12 September 2016 to Question 45147, what his Department's total spend has been to date.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","46322"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582644","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-09-26","<p>The Government publishes information about flights and other expenses incurred on Ministerial and senior official overseas trips on a quarterly basis.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2016-09-26T16:39:51.857Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582644/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582644/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582644/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-09-13","Department for Exiting the European Union: Travel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many international flights have been taken by (a) Ministers, (b) civil servants and (c) special advisers of his Department in an official capacity since his Department was created.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","46206"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582645","HM Treasury","false","2016-09-21","<p>To ensure stability and certainty in the period leading up to our departure from the EU, the Chancellor has announced that structural and investment fund projects in the UK that are signed before the Autumn Statement will be guaranteed. In addition, projects where UK organisations bid directly and competitively for EU funding, such as Horizon 2020 funded projects, will be guaranteed by the UK Government if the bids are won before our departure.</p><p> </p><p>Leaving the EU means we will want to take our own decisions about how to deliver the policy objectives previously targeted by EU funding. Over the coming months, we will consult closely with stakeholders to review all EU funding schemes in the round, to ensure that any ongoing funding commitments best serve the UK‘s national interest, while ensuring appropriate investor certainty.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-09-21T09:08:28.213Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582645/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582645/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582645/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-09-13","EU Grants and Loans: Tees Valley","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps he is taking to ensure that Teesside is not disadvantaged by the withdrawal of EU funding when the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Anna Turley","Redcar","Anna Turley","46136"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582646","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-09-27","<p>The Government publishes the relevant information on the costs of Ministerial and senior official hotel accommodation, as well as other expenses incurred on overseas trips, on a quarterly basis. Wherever possible Ministers and officials use overnight accommodation in UK Permanent Representations and Embassies to reduce the costs of travel abroad.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2016-09-27T12:01:34.977Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582646/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582646/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582646/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-09-13","Department for Exiting the European Union: Hotels","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how much his Department has spent on overnight hotel accommodation since it was created.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","46205"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582647","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-10-10","<p>The Department for Exiting the EU now has over 200 staff in London, plus the expertise of over 120 officials in Brussels, and we are still growing rapidly. We are not in a position to give a final total nor a breakdown by directorate as recruitment is ongoing.</p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones","46254 ; 46256","2016-10-10T16:24:03.547Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582647/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582647/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582647/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-09-13","Department for Exiting the European Union: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many staff, at what grades, his Department has recruited to work in the Permanent Secretary Office.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","46255"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582648","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-10-10","<p>The Department for Exiting the EU now has over 200 staff in London, plus the expertise of over 120 officials in Brussels, and we are still growing rapidly. We are not in a position to give a final total nor a breakdown by directorate as recruitment is ongoing.</p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones","46254 ; 46255","2016-10-10T16:24:03.61Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582648/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582648/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582648/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-09-13","Department for Exiting the European Union: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many of his Department's 24 vacant Deputy Director posts have been filled.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","46256"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582649","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-10-10","<p>The Department for Exiting the EU now has over 200 staff in London, plus the expertise of over 120 officials in Brussels, and we are still growing rapidly. We are not in a position to give a final total nor a breakdown by directorate as recruitment is ongoing.</p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones","46255 ; 46256","2016-10-10T16:24:03.48Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582649/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582649/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582649/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-09-13","Department for Exiting the European Union: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many staff, at what grades, his Department has recruited in the (a) Market Access Budget, (b) Justice, Security and Migration, (c) Cross-Government Policy and Coordination, (d) Strategy and Planning, (e) Trade and Partnership and (f) Analysis Directorate.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","46254"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582650","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-09-29","<p>The Financial Conduct Authority (FCA) prohibition on cold calling applies to financial promotion of mortgages by FCA regulated firms. Under the FCA rules, regulated entities (including mortgage providers) are not allowed to engage in real-time financial promotion of mortgages and therefore no legitimate market for telephone promotion and sales exists.</p><p>The Government tightened controls on cold calling earlier this year, when amending the Privacy and Electronic Communications Regulations (PECR), making it a requirement for organisations making direct marketing calls to display their Calling Line Identification (CLI). These controls need time to bed in before considering whether further changes, specific to pensions, are appropriate. If there is a case for change, the Government will take the necessary action.</p>",,"Lord Ashton of Hyde",,"2016-09-29T15:55:35.627Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582650/answer","Biography information for Lord Ashton of Hyde","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582650/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582650/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-09-13","Nuisance Calls","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government why cold calls regarding mortgages can be banned but not cold calls offering free pension reviews or unregulated pension investments.","false","Biography information for Baroness Altmann",,"Baroness Altmann","HL1833"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582651","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-09-27","<p>The Government has not made an estimate of the geographic origin of pension scams. Scams are often complex in nature and those reported to Action Fraud as taking place in the UK may have originated elsewhere.</p>",,"Lord Freud",,"2016-09-27T14:05:17.493Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582651/answer","Biography information for Lord Freud","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582651/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582651/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-13","Pensions: Fraud","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what estimate they have made of the percentage of pension scams in the UK that (1) originate overseas, and (2) are initiated by UK-based firms.","false","Biography information for Baroness Altmann",,"Baroness Altmann","HL1834"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582652","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-09-27","<p>DWP analysis suggests that at any one time around 10,000 men and 40,000 women have multiple jobs below the lower earnings limit (LEL) with combined earnings above it, but are not receiving any qualifying years towards the State Pension on those earnings.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>DWP analysis estimates that of the women with multiple jobs below the LEL but total earnings above it, around 30% are getting a childcare credit for their State Pension. Others in this group may also be receiving credits through another route or be paying voluntary national insurance contributions.</p>",,"Lord Freud","HL1836","2016-09-27T14:04:58.777Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582652/answer","Biography information for Lord Freud","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582652/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582652/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-13","State Retirement Pensions","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many (1) women, and (2) men, are working but do not receive any credit towards their National Insurance state pension each year, due to being in one or more jobs that pay less than the lower earnings limit.","false","Biography information for Baroness Altmann",,"Baroness Altmann","HL1835"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582653","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-09-27","<p>DWP analysis suggests that at any one time around 10,000 men and 40,000 women have multiple jobs below the lower earnings limit (LEL) with combined earnings above it, but are not receiving any qualifying years towards the State Pension on those earnings.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>DWP analysis estimates that of the women with multiple jobs below the LEL but total earnings above it, around 30% are getting a childcare credit for their State Pension. Others in this group may also be receiving credits through another route or be paying voluntary national insurance contributions.</p>",,"Lord Freud","HL1835","2016-09-27T14:04:58.813Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582653/answer","Biography information for Lord Freud","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582653/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582653/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-09-13","State Retirement Pensions","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how women who are in multiple part-time jobs, none of which pay more than the National Insurance lower earnings limit, are able to claim credit for their state pension.","false","Biography information for Baroness Altmann",,"Baroness Altmann","HL1836"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582654","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-09-27","<p>We have no plans to seek the establishment of an International Commission of inquiry to investigate allegations of forced organ harvesting in China.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-09-27T14:09:19.1Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582654/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582654/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582654/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-09-13","China: Prisoners","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they plan to work with other countries to seek the establishment of an international commission of inquiry to investigate allegations of forced organ harvesting in China.","false","Biography information for Lord Alton of Liverpool",,"Lord Alton of Liverpool","HL1837"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582655","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-09-27","<p>I refer the noble Lord to the answer the Parliamentary Undersecretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my Hon. Friend the Member for Reading West (Mr Sharma) gave on 14 September in response to Written Question 45143 from the Hon. Member for Strangford (Mr Jim Shannon), copied below for ease of reference:</p><p>“As My Rt Hon. Friend, the former Minister of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, Hugo Swire, stated to the house on the 12 July 2016, we have raised concerns about reports of organ harvesting, as well as about the torture and mistreatment of detainees, during the annual UK-China human rights dialogue. We will do so again at the next round. My officials also raised the issue with their Chinese counterparts on 1 September 2016. However, despite the fact that UK physicians always advise patients against, it is very difficult to prevent UK citizens travelling to less well-regulated countries to seek an organ transplant. Although numbers are not known, it is thought that very few patients in the UK choose to do so.”</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-09-27T14:10:05.63Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582655/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582655/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582655/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-09-13","China: Prisoners","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what consideration they have given to ways to prohibit British citizens from travelling to China for the purpose of obtaining an organ transplant until the practice of forced organ harvesting ceases.","false","Biography information for Lord Alton of Liverpool",,"Lord Alton of Liverpool","HL1838"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582656","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-09-26","<p>The method of mosquito control in other countries is not a matter routinely covered by FCO travel advice. Currently, specific UK health travel advice for Florida and the wider US is supplied by the National Travel Health Network and Centre, to which the FCO website country pages have links.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-09-26T13:18:18.26Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582656/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582656/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582656/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-09-13","USA: British Nationals Abroad","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, in the light of the use in Florida of the organophosphate insecticide Naled, which is banned in the EU, what advice they are giving to British citizens intending to visit Florida; and what steps they are taking to place that advice on the Foreign and Commonwealth Office website.","false","Biography information for Lord Blencathra",,"Lord Blencathra","HL1839"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582657","Home Office","false","2016-09-27","<p>The Government recently launched a community sponsorship scheme to enable community groups including charities, faith groups, churches and businesses to take on the role of supporting resettled refugees in the UK.</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford",,"2016-09-27T14:03:11.65Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582657/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582657/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582657/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-09-13","Refugees: Facilities","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what financial contribution they have received from the Church of England to fund the provision of facilities for refugees.","false","Biography information for Lord Blencathra",,"Lord Blencathra","HL1840"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582658","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-21","<p>Defence has no current plans in place to provide training in train driving, operating or management.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2016-09-21T15:53:55.93Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582658/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582658/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582658/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-13","Armed Forces: Railways","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what consideration they have given to putting in place immediate arrangements for members of the armed forces to be trained in train driving, operating and management.","false","Biography information for Lord Blencathra",,"Lord Blencathra","HL1841"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582659","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-22","<p>Service in Afghanistan is recognised by the Operational Service Medal. All those who deployed to Afghanistan will have been eligible to receive the medal if they met the qualifying criteria. There is a long-standing rule that decisions taken with regards to medallic recognition should not be revisited once five years have passed since the conclusion of a military operation. The 'five year' rule has been looked at by the Committee on the Grants of Honours, Decorations and Medals (HD Committee) on a number of occasions, and on each occasion it has concluded that the rule is sound and should not be changed.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2016-09-22T13:03:32.32Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582659/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582659/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582659/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-13","Afghanistan: Peacekeeping Operations","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what steps they are planning to take to honour the British soldiers who fought in Musa Qala in Afghanistan in the autumn of 2006.","false","Biography information for Lord Blencathra",,"Lord Blencathra","HL1842"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582660","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-09-27","<p>Individuals in each government department are responsible for the care of cats and any other animals residing in their buildings. We are mindful of our duties under the Animal Welfare Act, and this includes the provision of routine and emergency veterinary treatment. While no care or food costs for any animals in government buildings are funded by the public purse, these animals are supported and cared for thanks to voluntary fundraising.</p><p>I also refer my noble friend to the answer to him of 16 September 2016 to Question 1605.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Gardiner of Kimble",,"2016-09-27T13:52:23.493Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582660/answer","Biography information for Lord Gardiner of Kimble","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582660/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582660/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-09-13","Government Departments: Cats","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what arrangements they have put in place to ensure that there is proper routine and emergency veterinary treatment for government cats, and any other officially owned animals in government service.","false","Biography information for Lord Blencathra",,"Lord Blencathra","HL1843"
